# Moni – Project Overview

**Moni** is a local-first, privacy-focused personal finance app: wallets, transactions, analytics, and AI that turns natural language, receipt photos, and (Android) bank notifications into **reviewable transaction proposals** (`proposed_transactions` + a review UI — AI never writes to the ledger directly).

## Monorepo (Turborepo + pnpm)

```
apps/mobile/      Expo SDK 54 + expo-router — PRIMARY client (focus)
apps/backend/     Go + Gin AI gateway → Groq (focus)
apps/web/         Next.js 16 dashboard — ISOLATED, deprioritized
packages/types/   @repo/types — Zod schemas + inferred TS types
supabase/         Migrations, RLS, storage
docs/             ARCHITECTURE / SETUP / DATABASE / AI
```

Run: `pnpm --filter moni dev` / `pnpm --filter backend dev` / `pnpm --filter web dev`. Go integrates with turbo via package.json scripts (`go run` / `go vet` / `go test`).

## Architecture rules

- **Mobile syncs directly to Supabase** via Legend-State (`apps/mobile/lib/store/index.ts`) with MMKV persistence and soft deletes. There is NO PowerSync, NO SQLite/Drizzle, NO local LLM — do not reintroduce them.
- **Mobile and web never talk to each other.** Web's API routes serve only the web dashboard. Shared needs go through Supabase (data) or the Go backend (AI).
- **Go backend is stateless**: verifies Supabase user JWTs via JWKS (ES256), calls Groq, returns extractions. No database access.
- **Supabase keys**: new system only — `sb_publishable_...` in clients, `sb_secret_...` server-side. Never use legacy anon/service_role keys.
- **AI wire contract**: `apps/mobile/lib/ai/client/types.ts` ↔ `apps/backend/internal/extract/types.go` must stay in sync manually.

## Conventions

- TypeScript strict; all shared shapes as Zod schemas in `@repo/types`, types inferred — never duplicated
- Auth: Supabase JWT Bearer tokens; ES256 asymmetric signing
- Error responses: `{ error: string; details?: any }`
- Money: `DECIMAL(12,2)`, 3-letter ISO currency; UUID primary keys
- Designed for ~1000 users at minimal cost (Supabase free tier, Groq Developer tier, Cloud Run scale-to-zero)
